name: Sage CRM
description: Add a Sage CRM  Instance to connect your existing Sage account to the SageCRM Hub, allowing you to manage accounts, contacts, leads, opportunities, and users, etc. across multiple Sage Elements. You will need your Sage CRM account information to add an instance.

configuration.name: Lead Created field
configuration.description: Created Date fields for leads (using updated as created field may be null)

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Bulk Query Update
configuration.description: Update the bulk query to use the resource related name

configuration.name: Users Created field
configuration.description: Created Date fields for users (using updated as created field may be null)

configuration.name: Contacts Created field
configuration.description: Created Date field for contacts (using updated as created field may be null)

configuration.name: Opportunities Created field
configuration.description: Created Date field for opportunities (using updated as created field may be null)

configuration.name: Account Created field
configuration.description: Created Date fields for Accounts (using updated as created field may be null)

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Event poller refresh interval
configuration.description: Set time interval for polling application (in minutes)

configuration.name: Event Poller Resources Configuration
configuration.description: Event Poller Resources Configuration. The configuration is defined via JSON, an example of which is as follows - { "contacts": { "url": "/hubs/helpdesk/contacts", “idField”: “user.id”, “datesConfiguration”: { "updatedDateField": "user.updated_at", "updatedDateFormat": "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssX", “createdDateField”: “user.created_at”, “createdDateFormat": "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssX" }, "pageSize": 10000 } }

parameters.name: orderBy
parameters.description: Specifies the order of the result set. Valid parameters are asc or desc, i.e. Comp_CompanyId desc

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression. The following operators are supported: "="."!=","<=",<",">=",">","AND" and "OR", i.e. Comp_LibraryDir='ddddd'

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size. Defaults to 200 if not provided. Maximum of 2000

parameters.name: nextPage
parameters.description: The next page cursor, taken from the response header `elements-next-page-token`
